[In fact, the Japanese never deployed anthrax spores, but they did a
lot of experimentation at Unit 731 using human subjects -- "logs" --
and in one series using spores as a wound contaminant in shrapnel
devices. Anyone wanting to know more can go to:
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unit_731 or read Sheldon Harris's book
"Factories of death: Japanese biological warfare 1932-45 and the
American cover-up," Routledge, 1994. ISBN 0-415-09105-5 ISBN
0-415-93214-9. You don't want to read it before hoping to go to sleep.


